prompt:
What is the MATLAB code to extract and summarize the President's statement from a news article about the ongoing tensions in the Middle East using Latex data format?
Here's an example MATLAB code that can help with this task:
% Load the news article as a string
news_article = fileread('news_article.txt');
% Extract the President's statement using regular expressions
pres_statement = regexp(news_article, 'President:\s*(.*?)\n', 'tokens');
pres_statement = pres_statement{1}{1};
% Summarize the statement using the TextRank algorithm
summary = textrank(pres_statement);
% Print the summary in Latex format
fprintf('\\textbf{President\'s statement summary:} %s\n', summary);
Make sure to replace 'news_article.txt' with the actual file name and path of the news article you want to extract the President's statement from.

